{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2357,"text":"Good afternoon."},{"time":4229,"text":"There's a medical revolution\nhappening all around us,"},{"time":7000,"text":"and it's one that's going\nto help us conquer"},{"time":9120,"text":"some of society's most dreaded conditions,"},{"time":11144,"text":"including cancer."},{"time":13263,"text":"The revolution is called angiogenesis,"},{"time":16659,"text":"and it's based on the process\nthat our bodies use to grow blood vessels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21271,"text":"So why should we care about blood vessels?"},{"time":23350,"text":"Well, the human body\nis literally packed with them --"},{"time":26182,"text":"60,000 miles worth in a typical adult."},{"time":29650,"text":"End to end, that would form a line\nthat would circle the earth twice."},{"time":34079,"text":"The smallest blood vessels\nare called capillaries."},{"time":36810,"text":"We've got 19 billion of them\nin our bodies."},{"time":40377,"text":"And these are the vessels of life,"},{"time":43184,"text":"and as I'll show you,\nthey can also be the vessels of death."},{"time":48019,"text":"Now, the remarkable thing\nabout blood vessels"},{"time":50201,"text":"is that they have this ability"},{"time":52082,"text":"to adapt to whatever environment\nthey're growing in."},{"time":54819,"text":"For example, in the liver,\nthey form channels to detoxify the blood;"},{"time":58100,"text":"in the lungs, they line air sacs\nfor gas exchange."},{"time":60855,"text":"In muscle, they corkscrew,"},{"time":62618,"text":"so that muscles can contract\nwithout cutting off circulation."},{"time":65878,"text":"And in nerves, they course along\nlike power lines,"},{"time":68425,"text":"keeping those nerves alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70449,"text":"We get most of these blood vessels"},{"time":72504,"text":"when we're actually still in the womb."},{"time":74766,"text":"And what that means is that as adults,"},{"time":77000,"text":"blood vessels don't normally grow."},{"time":79271,"text":"Except in a few special circumstances."},{"time":82787,"text":"In women, blood vessels grow every month,"},{"time":85000,"text":"to build the lining of the uterus."},{"time":86841,"text":"During pregnancy, they form the placenta,"},{"time":89292,"text":"which connects mom and baby."},{"time":92029,"text":"And after injury, blood vessels\nactually have to grow under the scab"},{"time":96323,"text":"in order to heal a wound."},{"time":98000,"text":"And this is actually what it looks like,"},{"time":99951,"text":"hundreds of blood vessels, all growing\ntoward the center of the wound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104121,"text":"So the body has the ability to regulate"},{"time":106932,"text":"the amount of blood vessels\nthat are present at any given time."},{"time":110024,"text":"It does this through an elaborate\nand elegant system of checks and balances,"},{"time":114436,"text":"stimulators and inhibitors\nof angiogenesis,"},{"time":117325,"text":"such that, when we need\na brief burst of blood vessels,"},{"time":120000,"text":"the body can do this\nby releasing stimulators,"},{"time":123000,"text":"proteins called angiogenic factors,"},{"time":125222,"text":"that act as natural fertilizer,\nand stimulate new blood vessels to sprout."},{"time":129412,"text":"When those excess vessels\nare no longer needed,"},{"time":131677,"text":"the body prunes them back to baseline,"},{"time":134288,"text":"using naturally-occurring\ninhibitors of angiogenesis."},{"time":138000,"text":"There are other situations\nwhere we start beneath the baseline,"},{"time":141317,"text":"and we need to grow more blood vessels,\njust to get back to normal levels --"},{"time":144993,"text":"for example, after an injury --"},{"time":146520,"text":"and the body can do that too,\nbut only to that normal level,"},{"time":149395,"text":"that set point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151112,"text":"But what we now know,\nis that for a number of diseases,"},{"time":154000,"text":"there are defects in the system,"},{"time":156409,"text":"where the body can't prune back\nextra blood vessels,"},{"time":158934,"text":"or can't grow enough new ones\nin the right place at the right time."},{"time":162884,"text":"And in these situations,\nangiogenesis is out of balance."},{"time":167193,"text":"And when angiogenesis is out of balance,"},{"time":169145,"text":"a myriad of diseases result."},{"time":171304,"text":"For example, insufficient angiogenesis --\nnot enough blood vessels --"},{"time":175000,"text":"leads to wounds\nthat don't heal, heart attacks,"},{"time":178000,"text":"legs without circulation,\ndeath from stroke,"},{"time":180639,"text":"nerve damage."},{"time":182457,"text":"And on the other end,\nexcessive angiogenesis --"},{"time":184798,"text":"too many blood vessels -- drives disease,"},{"time":186999,"text":"and we see this in cancer, blindness,"},{"time":189611,"text":"arthritis, obesity, Alzheimer's disease."},{"time":193306,"text":"In total, there are more\nthan 70 major diseases"},{"time":196473,"text":"affecting more than a billion\npeople worldwide,"},{"time":198966,"text":"that all look on the surface to be\ndifferent from one another,"},{"time":201958,"text":"but all actually share\nabnormal angiogenesis"},{"time":204800,"text":"as their common denominator."},{"time":207371,"text":"And this realization is allowing\nus to re-conceptualize"},{"time":210472,"text":"the way that we actually\napproach these diseases,"},{"time":212908,"text":"by controlling angiogenesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215829,"text":"Now, I'm going to focus on cancer,"},{"time":217762,"text":"because angiogenesis\nis a hallmark of cancer --"},{"time":221253,"text":"every type of cancer."},{"time":223253,"text":"So here we go."},{"time":224946,"text":"This is a tumor: dark, gray, ominous\nmass growing inside a brain."},{"time":228860,"text":"And under the microscope,"},{"time":230133,"text":"you can see hundreds\nof these brown-stained blood vessels,"},{"time":233170,"text":"capillaries that are feeding cancer cells,"},{"time":235241,"text":"bringing oxygen and nutrients."},{"time":238289,"text":"But cancers don't start out like this,"},{"time":240392,"text":"and in fact, cancers don't start out\nwith a blood supply."},{"time":243691,"text":"They start out as small,\nmicroscopic nests of cells,"},{"time":247351,"text":"that can only grow to one half\na cubic millimeter in size."},{"time":251679,"text":"That's the tip of a ballpoint pen."},{"time":253851,"text":"Then they can't get any larger\nbecause they don't have a blood supply,"},{"time":257185,"text":"so they don't have\nenough oxygen or nutrients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259364,"text":"In fact, we're probably forming\nthese microscopic cancers"},{"time":262713,"text":"all the time in our body."},{"time":264879,"text":"Autopsy studies from people\nwho died in car accidents"},{"time":268465,"text":"have shown that about 40 percent of women\nbetween the ages of 40 and 50"},{"time":273315,"text":"actually have microscopic\ncancers in their breasts."},{"time":277220,"text":"About 50 percent of men\nin their 50s and 60s"},{"time":279585,"text":"have microscopic prostate cancers,"},{"time":282138,"text":"and virtually 100 percent of us,\nby the time we reach our 70s,"},{"time":285829,"text":"will have microscopic cancers\ngrowing in our thyroid."},{"time":289320,"text":"Yet, without a blood supply,"},{"time":291000,"text":"most of these cancers\nwill never become dangerous."},{"time":295407,"text":"Dr. Judah Folkman, who was my mentor"},{"time":297637,"text":"and who was the pioneer\nof the angiogenesis field,"},{"time":300057,"text":"once called this \"cancer without disease.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":304625,"text":"So the body's ability\nto balance angiogenesis,"},{"time":307454,"text":"when it's working properly,"},{"time":309000,"text":"prevents blood vessels\nfrom feeding cancers."},{"time":311280,"text":"And this turns out to be"},{"time":313000,"text":"one of our most important\ndefense mechanisms"},{"time":315800,"text":"against cancer."},{"time":318212,"text":"In fact, if you actually\nblock angiogenesis"},{"time":320497,"text":"and prevent blood vessels\nfrom ever reaching cancer cells,"},{"time":323290,"text":"tumors simply can't grow up."},{"time":324715,"text":"But once angiogenesis occurs,"},{"time":326492,"text":"cancers can grow exponentially."},{"time":329389,"text":"And this is actually how a cancer\ngoes from being harmless,"},{"time":333722,"text":"to being deadly."},{"time":335658,"text":"Cancer cells mutate,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and they gain the ability to release\nlots of those angiogenic factors,"},{"time":340311,"text":"natural fertilizer,"},{"time":341506,"text":"that tip the balance in favor\nof blood vessels invading the cancer."},{"time":344976,"text":"And once those vessels invade the cancer,"},{"time":347000,"text":"it can expand,\nit can invade local tissues,"},{"time":350000,"text":"and the same vessels\nthat are feeding tumors"},{"time":352325,"text":"allow cancer cells to exit\ninto the circulation as metastases."},{"time":357428,"text":"And unfortunately,\nthis late stage of cancer"},{"time":360206,"text":"is the one at which\nit's most likely to be diagnosed,"},{"time":364190,"text":"when angiogenesis is already turned on,"},{"time":366229,"text":"and cancer cells are growing like wild."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369737,"text":"So, if angiogenesis is a tipping point"},{"time":373866,"text":"between a harmless cancer\nand a harmful one,"},{"time":377000,"text":"then one major part\nof the angiogenesis revolution"},{"time":380298,"text":"is a new approach to treating cancer"},{"time":382077,"text":"by cutting off the blood supply."},{"time":384909,"text":"We call this antiangiogenic therapy,"},{"time":388141,"text":"and it's completely different\nfrom chemotherapy,"},{"time":390443,"text":"because it selectively aims"},{"time":392347,"text":"at the blood vessels\nthat are feeding the cancers."},{"time":395384,"text":"We can do this because tumor blood vessels\nare unlike normal, healthy vessels"},{"time":399843,"text":"we see in other places of the body --"},{"time":401657,"text":"they're abnormal,\nthey're very poorly constructed,"},{"time":404805,"text":"and because of that,\nthey're highly vulnerable"},{"time":407083,"text":"to treatments that target them."},{"time":410666,"text":"In effect, when we give cancer patients\nantiangiogenic therapy --"},{"time":414222,"text":"here, an experimental drug for a glioma,"},{"time":417230,"text":"which is a type of brain tumor --"},{"time":419000,"text":"you can see that there are\ndramatic changes that occur"},{"time":421806,"text":"when the tumor is being starved."},{"time":424703,"text":"Here's a woman with a breast cancer,"},{"time":426631,"text":"being treated with the antiangiogenic\ndrug called Avastin,"},{"time":429579,"text":"which is FDA approved."},{"time":431571,"text":"And you can see\nthat the halo of blood flow"},{"time":434288,"text":"disappears after treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437463,"text":"Well, I've just shown you\ntwo very different types of cancer"},{"time":441000,"text":"that both responded\nto antiangiogenic therapy."},{"time":444166,"text":"So a few years ago, I asked myself,"},{"time":446349,"text":"\"Can we take this one step further\nand treat other cancers,"},{"time":450309,"text":"even in other species?\""},{"time":453888,"text":"So here is a nine year-old\nboxer named Milo,"},{"time":456302,"text":"who had a very aggressive tumor"},{"time":458000,"text":"called a malignant neurofibroma\ngrowing on his shoulder."},{"time":461032,"text":"It invaded into his lungs."},{"time":462641,"text":"His veterinarian only gave him\nthree months to live."},{"time":465149,"text":"So we created a cocktail\nof antiangiogenic drugs"},{"time":468000,"text":"that could be mixed into his dog food,"},{"time":470000,"text":"as well as an antiangiogenic cream,"},{"time":472277,"text":"that could be applied\non the surface of the tumor."},{"time":475277,"text":"And within a few weeks of treatment,"},{"time":477436,"text":"we were able to slow down\nthat cancer's growth,"},{"time":479786,"text":"such that we were ultimately\nable to extend Milo’s survival"},{"time":483063,"text":"to six times what the veterinarian\nhad initially predicted,"},{"time":486706,"text":"all with a very good quality of life."},{"time":489306,"text":"And we've subsequently treated\nmore than 600 dogs."},{"time":492000,"text":"We have about a 60 percent response rate,"},{"time":494294,"text":"and improved survival for these pets"},{"time":496730,"text":"that were about to be euthanized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499254,"text":"So let me show you a couple\nof even more interesting examples."},{"time":503154,"text":"This is 20-year-old dolphin\nliving in Florida,"},{"time":505503,"text":"and she had these lesions in her mouth"},{"time":507678,"text":"that, over the course of three years,"},{"time":509488,"text":"developed into invasive\nsquamous cell cancers."},{"time":512610,"text":"So we created an antiangiogenic paste."},{"time":515372,"text":"We had it painted on top of the cancer\nthree times a week."},{"time":519299,"text":"And over the course of seven months,"},{"time":521522,"text":"the cancers completely disappeared,"},{"time":523260,"text":"and the biopsies came back as normal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527633,"text":"Here's a cancer growing on the lip"},{"time":529363,"text":"of a Quarter Horse named Guinness."},{"time":531355,"text":"It's a very, very deadly type\nof cancer called an angiosarcoma."},{"time":534482,"text":"It had already spread to his lymph nodes,"},{"time":536474,"text":"so we used an antiangiogenic\nskin cream for the lip,"},{"time":539522,"text":"and the oral cocktail, so we could treat\nfrom the inside as well as the outside."},{"time":544127,"text":"And over the course of six months,"},{"time":546278,"text":"he experienced a complete remission."},{"time":549333,"text":"And here he is six years later,"},{"time":552508,"text":"Guinness, with his very happy owner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555413,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"Now obviously, antiangiogenic therapy\ncould be used for a wide range of cancers."},{"time":563250,"text":"And in fact, the first\npioneering treatments"},{"time":565559,"text":"for people as well as dogs,"},{"time":567154,"text":"are already becoming available."},{"time":568814,"text":"There are 12 different drugs,\n11 different cancer types."},{"time":572736,"text":"But the real question is:"},{"time":574000,"text":"How well do these work in practice?"},{"time":576283,"text":"So here's actually\nthe patient survival data"},{"time":579420,"text":"from eight different types of cancer."},{"time":581229,"text":"The bars represent survival time"},{"time":583712,"text":"taken from the era in which\nthere was only chemotherapy,"},{"time":587276,"text":"or surgery, or radiation available."},{"time":589934,"text":"But starting in 2004,"},{"time":592331,"text":"when antiangiogenic therapies\nfirst became available,"},{"time":594981,"text":"you can see that there has been a 70\nto 100 percent improvement in survival"},{"time":599915,"text":"for people with kidney cancer,\nmultiple myeloma,"},{"time":603100,"text":"colorectal cancer,\nand gastrointestinal stromal tumors."},{"time":607179,"text":"That's impressive."},{"time":608981,"text":"But for other tumors and cancer types,"},{"time":611964,"text":"the improvements have only been modest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615000,"text":"So I started asking myself,"},{"time":616908,"text":"\"Why haven't we been able to do better?\""},{"time":620161,"text":"And the answer, to me, is obvious:"},{"time":622312,"text":"we're treating cancer\ntoo late in the game,"},{"time":624638,"text":"when it's already established,"},{"time":626321,"text":"and oftentimes, it's already\nspread or metastasized."},{"time":629472,"text":"And as a doctor,"},{"time":630647,"text":"I know that once a disease progresses\nto an advanced stage,"},{"time":634513,"text":"achieving a cure can be difficult,\nif not impossible."},{"time":639544,"text":"So I went back to the biology\nof angiogenesis, and started thinking:"},{"time":645452,"text":"Could the answer to cancer\nbe preventing angiogenesis,"},{"time":650478,"text":"beating cancer at its own game,"},{"time":652367,"text":"so the cancers could never\nbecome dangerous?"},{"time":656414,"text":"This could help healthy people,"},{"time":658120,"text":"as well as people who've already\nbeaten cancer once or twice,"},{"time":661851,"text":"and want to find a way\nto keep it from coming back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665196,"text":"So to look for a way to prevent\nangiogenesis in cancer,"},{"time":668000,"text":"I went back to look at cancer's causes."},{"time":670572,"text":"And what really intrigued me,"},{"time":672000,"text":"was when I saw that diet\naccounts for 30 to 35 percent"},{"time":676357,"text":"of environmentally-caused cancers."},{"time":679133,"text":"Now the obvious thing is to think about\nwhat we could remove from our diet,"},{"time":682871,"text":"what to strip out, take away."},{"time":685442,"text":"But I actually took\na completely opposite approach,"},{"time":688257,"text":"and began asking: What could\nwe be adding to our diet"},{"time":691670,"text":"that's naturally antiangiogenic,"},{"time":694175,"text":"and that could boost\nthe body's defense system,"},{"time":696532,"text":"and beat back those blood vessels\nthat are feeding cancers?"},{"time":699635,"text":"In other words, can we eat\nto starve cancer?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":703056,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":704405,"text":"Well, the answer is yes,\nand I'm going to show you how."},{"time":707174,"text":"And our search for this\nhas taken us to the market,"},{"time":710562,"text":"the farm and to the spice cabinet,"},{"time":712435,"text":"because what we've discovered"},{"time":713921,"text":"is that Mother Nature\nhas laced a large number"},{"time":716215,"text":"of foods and beverages and herbs"},{"time":718000,"text":"with naturally-occurring\ninhibitors of angiogenesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722378,"text":"Here's a test system we developed."},{"time":724101,"text":"At the center is a ring"},{"time":725284,"text":"from which hundreds of blood vessels\nare growing out in a starburst fashion."},{"time":728918,"text":"And we can use this system\nto test dietary factors"},{"time":731861,"text":"at concentrations\nthat are obtainable by eating."},{"time":735709,"text":"Let me show you what happens"},{"time":737122,"text":"when we put in an extract from red grapes."},{"time":739884,"text":"The active ingredient is resveratrol,"},{"time":742000,"text":"it's also found in red wine."},{"time":744171,"text":"This inhibits abnormal angiogenesis,"},{"time":747000,"text":"by 60 percent."},{"time":749277,"text":"Here's what happens when we added\nan extract from strawberries."},{"time":752468,"text":"It potently inhibits angiogenesis."},{"time":755720,"text":"And extract from soybeans."},{"time":758725,"text":"And here is a growing list"},{"time":760670,"text":"of antiangiogenic foods and beverages\nthat we're interested in studying."},{"time":765312,"text":"For each food type,"},{"time":767326,"text":"we believe that there are\ndifferent potencies"},{"time":769572,"text":"within different strains and varietals."},{"time":771946,"text":"And we want to measure this because,"},{"time":774201,"text":"well, while you're eating a strawberry"},{"time":776439,"text":"or drinking tea,"},{"time":777940,"text":"why not select the one that's most potent"},{"time":780000,"text":"for preventing cancer?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":782000,"text":"So here are four different teas\nthat we've tested."},{"time":785100,"text":"They're all common ones:\nChinese jasmine, Japanese sencha,"},{"time":789000,"text":"Earl Grey and a special blend\nthat we prepared,"},{"time":791644,"text":"and you can see clearly\nthat the teas vary in their potency,"},{"time":795369,"text":"from less potent to more potent."},{"time":798742,"text":"But what's very cool"},{"time":800250,"text":"is when we combine\nthe two less potent teas together,"},{"time":804023,"text":"the combination, the blend,\nis more potent than either one alone."},{"time":809285,"text":"This means there's food synergy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814374,"text":"Here's some more data from our testing."},{"time":816287,"text":"Now in the lab, we can\nsimulate tumor angiogenesis,"},{"time":819223,"text":"represented here in a black bar."},{"time":821238,"text":"And using this system, we can test\nthe potency of cancer drugs."},{"time":824330,"text":"So the shorter the bar,"},{"time":825886,"text":"the less angiogenesis -- that's good."},{"time":829000,"text":"And here are some common drugs"},{"time":830863,"text":"that have been associated with reducing\nthe risk of cancer in people."},{"time":835000,"text":"Statins, nonsteroidal\nanti-inflammatory drugs,"},{"time":837825,"text":"and a few others --\nthey inhibit angiogenesis, too."},{"time":842000,"text":"And here are the dietary factors"},{"time":844000,"text":"going head-to-head against these drugs."},{"time":846919,"text":"You can see they clearly hold their own,"},{"time":849000,"text":"and in some cases, they're more potent\nthan the actual drugs."},{"time":852751,"text":"Soy, parsley, garlic, grapes, berries."},{"time":857267,"text":"I could go home and cook a tasty meal\nusing these ingredients."},{"time":861580,"text":"Imagine if we could create\nthe world's first rating system,"},{"time":865572,"text":"in which we could score foods"},{"time":867143,"text":"according to their antiangiogenic,\ncancer-preventative properties."},{"time":871307,"text":"And that's what we're doing right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874339,"text":"Now, I've shown you a bunch of lab data,"},{"time":876289,"text":"and so the real question is:"},{"time":878097,"text":"What is the evidence in people"},{"time":880399,"text":"that eating certain foods can reduce\nangiogenesis in cancer?"},{"time":885240,"text":"Well, the best example I know"},{"time":887000,"text":"is a study of 79,000 men\nfollowed over 20 years,"},{"time":891085,"text":"in which it was found that men\nwho consumed cooked tomatoes"},{"time":893950,"text":"two to three times a week,"},{"time":895464,"text":"had up to a 50 percent reduction"},{"time":898000,"text":"in their risk of developing\nprostate cancer."},{"time":901106,"text":"Now, we know that tomatoes\nare a good source of lycopene,"},{"time":904436,"text":"and lycopene is antiangiogenic."},{"time":907357,"text":"But what's even more\ninteresting from this study,"},{"time":909699,"text":"is that in those men who did\ndevelop prostate cancer,"},{"time":912280,"text":"those who ate more\nservings of tomato sauce,"},{"time":915098,"text":"actually had fewer blood vessels\nfeeding their cancer."},{"time":919000,"text":"So this human study is a prime example"},{"time":921442,"text":"of how antiangiogenic substances present\nin food and consumed at practical levels,"},{"time":926392,"text":"can have an impact on cancer."},{"time":928676,"text":"And we're now studying\nthe role of a healthy diet --"},{"time":932000,"text":"with Dean Ornish at UCSF\nand Tufts University --"},{"time":935000,"text":"the role of this healthy diet\non markers of angiogenesis"},{"time":938450,"text":"that we can find in the bloodstream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940700,"text":"Obviously, what I've shared with you\nhas some far-ranging implications,"},{"time":944446,"text":"even beyond cancer research."},{"time":946000,"text":"Because if we're right,\nit could impact consumer education,"},{"time":949276,"text":"food services, public health"},{"time":951117,"text":"and even the insurance industry."},{"time":953340,"text":"And in fact, some insurance companies"},{"time":955150,"text":"are already beginning\nto think along these lines."},{"time":957484,"text":"Check out this ad from BlueCross\nBlueShield of Minnesota."},{"time":961411,"text":"For many people around the world,"},{"time":963110,"text":"dietary cancer prevention\nmay be the only practical solution,"},{"time":966896,"text":"because not everybody can afford\nexpensive end-stage cancer treatments,"},{"time":970369,"text":"but everybody could benefit\nfrom a healthy diet"},{"time":973084,"text":"based on local, sustainable,\nantiangiogenic crops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978245,"text":"Now, finally,"},{"time":980467,"text":"I've talked to you about food,"},{"time":982174,"text":"and I've talked to you about cancer,"},{"time":984000,"text":"so there's just one more disease\nthat I have to tell you about,"},{"time":987324,"text":"and that's obesity."},{"time":989000,"text":"Because it turns out\nthat adipose tissue -- fat --"},{"time":993000,"text":"is highly angiogenesis-dependent."},{"time":995626,"text":"And like a tumor, fat grows\nwhen blood vessels grow."},{"time":998420,"text":"So the question is:"},{"time":999662,"text":"Can we shrink fat\nby cutting off its blood supply?"},{"time":1003470,"text":"The top curve shows the body weight\nof a genetically obese mouse"},{"time":1007999,"text":"that eats nonstop until it turns fat,"},{"time":1011173,"text":"like this furry tennis ball."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012851,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1014061,"text":"And the bottom curve\nis the weight of a normal mouse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1017276,"text":"If you take the obese mouse"},{"time":1018602,"text":"and give it an angiogenesis\ninhibitor, it loses weight."},{"time":1021299,"text":"Stop the treatment, gains the weight back.\nRestart the treatment, loses the weight."},{"time":1025265,"text":"Stop the treatment,\nit gains the weight back."},{"time":1027400,"text":"And, in fact, you can cycle\nthe weight up and down"},{"time":1029781,"text":"simply by inhibiting angiogenesis."},{"time":1031797,"text":"So this approach that we're taking\nfor cancer prevention"},{"time":1034566,"text":"may also have an application for obesity."},{"time":1038087,"text":"The truly interesting thing about this"},{"time":1040215,"text":"is that we can't take these obese mice"},{"time":1042215,"text":"and make them lose more weight"},{"time":1044000,"text":"than what the normal mouse's weight\nis supposed to be."},{"time":1047221,"text":"In other words,\nwe can't create supermodel mice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050254,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051539,"text":"And this speaks to the role\nof angiogenesis"},{"time":1053607,"text":"in regulating healthy set points."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1056504,"text":"Albert Szent-Györgi once said,"},{"time":1058435,"text":"\"Discovery consists of seeing\nwhat everyone has seen,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"and thinking what no one has thought.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063261,"text":"I hope I've convinced you"},{"time":1064715,"text":"that for diseases like cancer,\nobesity and other conditions,"},{"time":1067999,"text":"there may be a great power"},{"time":1069845,"text":"in attacking their common\ndenominator: angiogenesis."},{"time":1072996,"text":"And that's what I think\nthe world needs now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075076,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076251,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1086390,"text":"June Cohen: I have\na quick question for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1088486,"text":"JC: So these drugs aren't exactly\nin mainstream cancer treatments right now."},{"time":1093388,"text":"For anyone out here who has cancer,\nwhat would you recommend?"},{"time":1097000,"text":"Do you recommend pursuing these\ntreatments now, for most cancer patients?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1100742,"text":"William Li: There are\nantiangiogenic treatments"},{"time":1102974,"text":"that are FDA approved,"},{"time":1104409,"text":"and if you're a cancer patient,"},{"time":1106417,"text":"or working for one or advocating for one,\nyou should ask about them."},{"time":1110352,"text":"And there are many clinical trials."},{"time":1113000,"text":"The Angiogenesis Foundation\nis following almost 300 companies,"},{"time":1116000,"text":"and there are about 100 more\ndrugs in that pipeline."},{"time":1120425,"text":"So, consider the approved ones,"},{"time":1122000,"text":"look for clinical trials,"},{"time":1123722,"text":"but then between\nwhat the doctor can do for you,"},{"time":1126245,"text":"we need to start asking\nwhat can we do for ourselves."},{"time":1128806,"text":"This is one of the themes\nI'm talking about:"},{"time":1130910,"text":"We can empower ourselves"},{"time":1132089,"text":"to do the things that doctors\ncan't do for us,"},{"time":1134300,"text":"which is to use knowledge and take action."},{"time":1136396,"text":"And if Mother Nature\nhas given us some clues,"},{"time":1139000,"text":"we think there might be a new future\nin the value of how we eat,"},{"time":1143276,"text":"and what we eat is really\nour chemotherapy three times a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1146398,"text":"JC: Right. And along those lines,"},{"time":1148471,"text":"for people who might have\nrisk factors for cancer,"},{"time":1151000,"text":"would you recommend pursuing\nany treatments prophylactically,"},{"time":1154263,"text":"or simply pursuing the right diet,"},{"time":1156495,"text":"with lots of tomato sauce?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1158279,"text":"WL: Well, you know, there's abundant\nepidemiological evidence,"},{"time":1161501,"text":"and I think in the information age,"},{"time":1163216,"text":"it doesn't take long to go\nto a credible source like PubMed,"},{"time":1166079,"text":"the National Library of Medicine,"},{"time":1167689,"text":"to look for epidemiological studies\nfor cancer risk reduction"},{"time":1170999,"text":"based on diet and based\non common medications."},{"time":1173893,"text":"And that's certainly something\nthat anybody can look into."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1176664,"text":"JC: Okay. Well, thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1178334,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}